USSC palettes

Source: R/ussc_colours.R
ussc_palettes_list.Rd

This function prints the `ussc` colors as organised by political party or dark or light color scheme.

ussc_palettes_list

Format

An object of class list of length 11.

Examples

ussc::ussc_palettes_list
#> $main
#>  dark blue light blue     orange 
#>  "#2f2665"  "#4aace9"  "#ee4627" 
#> 
#> $blue
#> light blue  dark blue 
#>  "#4aace9"  "#2f2665" 
#> 
#> $light_blue_to_orange
#> light blue     orange 
#>  "#4aace9"  "#ee4627" 
#> 
#> $dark_blue_to_orange
#> dark blue    orange 
#> "#2f2665" "#ee4627" 
#> 
#> $light
#> light blue     orange       pink       grey 
#>  "#4aace9"  "#ee4627"  "#e1a6a0"  "#c0c0c0" 
#> 
#> $mixed
#>  dark blue light blue     orange       pink       grey      green 
#>  "#2f2665"  "#4aace9"  "#ee4627"  "#e1a6a0"  "#c0c0c0"  "#94c497" 
#> 
#> $uspol
#>    Democrat Independent  Republican 
#>   "#009de3"   "#c8c8c8"   "#ed1b35" 
#> 
#> $auspol
#>   Coalition      Greens       Labor 
#>   "#009de3" "darkgreen"   "#ed1b35" 
#> 
#> $ussc_survey_uspol
#>       All   Clinton  Other/NV     Trump 
#> "#696969" "#009de3" "#C0C0C0" "#ed1b35" 
#> 
#> $ussc_survey_auspol
#>         All   Coalition      Greens       Labor    Other/NV 
#>   "#696969"   "#009de3" "darkgreen"   "#ed1b35"   "#C0C0C0" 
#> 
#> $ussc_survey_pol
#>         All     Clinton   Coalition      Greens       Labor    Other/NV 
#>   "#696969"   "#009de3"   "#009de3" "darkgreen"   "#ed1b35"   "#C0C0C0" 
#>       Trump 
#>   "#ed1b35" 
#>
